# Environment Variables - Email Verification Setup

## Required Environment Variables

### Database
```
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database_name
# or
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database_name
# or
DATABASE_URL=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database_name
```

### JWT & Security (Dual Token Authentication)
```
# Access token (short-lived) - used for API requests
JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=your_super_secret_access_token_key_change_this

# Refresh token (long-lived) - used to refresh access tokens
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=your_super_secret_refresh_token_key_change_this

# Legacy support (falls back to JWT_SECRET if JWT_ACCESS_SECRET not set)
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_change_this_in_production

NODE_ENV=production  # or development
```

### Frontend URL (Important for email links)
```
FRONTEND_URL=https://yourdomain.com
# Local development:
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

### Email Service Configuration

#### Option 1: Brevo (Recommended for Production)
```
BREVO_API_KEY=xkeysib-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
BREVO_SMTP_USER=your-brevo-login@example.com  # Optional, defaults to 'apikey'
EMAIL_FROM=noreply@yourdomain.com
```

#### Option 2: SendGrid
```
SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
EMAIL_FROM=noreply@yourdomain.com
```

#### Option 3: SMTP (Any email provider)
```
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_SECURE=false
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
EMAIL_FROM=noreply@yourdomain.com
```

#### Option 3: Ethereal Email (Testing/Development)
- Leave all SMTP/SENDGRID variables empty or commented out
- The system will automatically use Ethereal Email for testing
- Check console for test account credentials

### Frontend (Next.js)
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://yourdomain.com
# or for local development:
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Local Development (.env.local)
```bash
# Copy this to .env.local and fill in your values
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# For email testing (optional - uses Ethereal Email by default)
# SMTP_HOST=
# SMTP_PORT=
# SMTP_USER=
# SMTP_PASS=
```

### 2. Production (.env.production or .env)
```bash
MONGODB_URI=your_production_mongodb_url
JWT_SECRET=your_production_secret_key
FRONTEND_URL=https://yourdomain.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://yourdomain.com
NODE_ENV=production

# Use Brevo for production (recommended)
BREVO_API_KEY=your_brevo_api_key
BREVO_SMTP_USER=your-brevo-login@example.com  # Optional
EMAIL_FROM=noreply@yourdomain.com
```

### 3. Vercel Deployment
In Vercel project settings → Environment Variables, add:
- `MONGODB_URI`
- `JWT_SECRET`
- `FRONTEND_URL` (e.g., https://airswift.vercel.app)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (same as FRONTEND_URL)
- `BREVO_API_KEY` (recommended) or `SENDGRID_API_KEY`
- `BREVO_SMTP_USER` (optional)
- `EMAIL_FROM`
- `NODE_ENV=production`

### 4. Render Deployment
In Render dashboard → Environment, add the same variables as Vercel

## Email Provider Setup

### Gmail with App Password
1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication on Gmail
2. Go to [Google Account → App Passwords](https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords)
3. Select Mail and Windows Computer
4. Copy the generated password
5. Use:
   ```
   SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
   SMTP_PORT=587
   SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
   SMTP_PASS=generated_app_password
   ```

### SendGrid
1. Create account at [SendGrid](https://sendgrid.com)
2. Go to Settings → API Keys
3. Create new API key
4. Use:
   ```
   SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.your_key
   EMAIL_FROM=noreply@yourdomain.com  (must be verified sender)
   ```

### Local Testing with Ethereal Email
- No configuration needed! Leave SMTP/SENDGRID empty
- Check server console for test email account
- Opens test email preview automatically

## Token Configuration

### Email Verification Tokens
Email verification tokens expire after **10 minutes** by default.
To change this, edit `/src/lib/emailVerificationHelper.ts`:

```typescript
// Change expiryMinutes parameter (default: 10)
const { token, hashedToken, expiresAt } = generateVerificationToken(30) // 30 minutes
```

### Access Tokens
Short-lived tokens valid for **15 minutes** used for API requests.
Change in:
- `/src/lib/authController.ts` - expiresIn: '15m'
- `/src/pages/api/auth/verify.ts` - expiresIn: '15m'

### Refresh Tokens
Long-lived tokens valid for **7 days** used to obtain new access tokens.
Change in:
- `/src/lib/authController.ts` - expiresIn: '7d'
- `/src/pages/api/auth/verify.ts` - expiresIn: '7d'
- `/src/pages/api/auth/refresh.ts` - expiresIn: '7d'

### Password Reset Tokens
Reset tokens expire after **1 hour**.
Change in `/src/lib/emailVerificationHelper.ts`:

```typescript
const { token, hashedToken, expiresAt } = generateVerificationToken(60) // 60 minutes
```

## Security Checklist

✅ Never commit `.env.local` or actual secrets to git
✅ Use strong JWT_SECRET (32+ characters)
✅ Use HTTPS in production
✅ Enable SendGrid/SMTP in production only
✅ Verify sender email in SendGrid
✅ Keep API keys secret
✅ Use app passwords (not regular passwords) for Gmail
✅ Regenerate tokens if leaked

## Troubleshooting

### "MongoDB connection error"
- Check `MONGODB_URI` or `MONGO_URI` is correct
- Ensure MongoDB is running
- Check IP whitelist in MongoDB Atlas

### "Email not sent"
- Verify `SENDGRID_API_KEY` or SMTP credentials
- Check `EMAIL_FROM` is correct
- For Gmail: enable "Less secure app access" or use app password
- Check email logs in SendGrid dashboard

### "Token is undefined"
- Ensure `FRONTEND_URL` is set
- Token is generated via `generateVerificationToken()` in registration endpoint
- Check backend logs for errors

### "Link doesn't work"
- Verify `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` matches backend URL
- Check token isn't URL-encoded incorrectly
- Test with curl: `curl "{backend_url}/api/auth/verify?token=..."`

## Files Using These Variables

- `/src/lib/emailService.ts` - All email variables
- `/src/pages/api/auth/register.ts` - Generates verification tokens
- `/src/pages/api/auth/verify.ts` - Validates tokens, generates access & refresh tokens
- `/src/pages/api/auth/refresh.ts` - Refreshes access tokens using refresh tokens
- `/src/lib/authController.ts` - JWT_ACCESS_SECRET, JWT_REFRESH_SECRET
- `/src/lib/middleware/authMiddleware.ts` - JWT_ACCESS_SECRET verification
- `/src/utils/apiFetch.ts` - API interceptor for token refresh
- `/src/pages/verify.tsx` - NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL
- `/src/services/authService.ts` - NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL, token storage
